From: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: media: intel: ipu-bridge: fix double brace typo in ipu_bridge_check_ivsc_dev

A stray extra opening brace on line 195 of ipu-bridge.c causes all
subsequent static functions to be parsed as nested functions inside
ipu_bridge_check_ivsc_dev(). GCC 15 (Gentoo) tolerates this, but
GCC 14 and earlier reject it with "invalid storage class for function".

Fix by removing the duplicate brace.

Affects: gentoo-sources-6.12.58

--- a/drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu-bridge.c
+++ b/drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu-bridge.c
@@ -192,7 +192,7 @@
 	adev = ipu_bridge_get_ivsc_acpi_dev(sensor_adev);
 	if (adev) {
 		csi_dev = ipu_bridge_get_ivsc_csi_dev(adev);
-		if (!csi_dev) { {
+		if (!csi_dev) {
 			acpi_dev_put(adev);
 			dev_err(ADEV_DEV(adev), "Failed to find MEI CSI dev\n");
 			return -ENODEV;
